DESCRIPTION:Looking for something to do after school? Come out to our Afte
 r School Club and learn new things\, make stuff\, meet other kids and have
  fun! For ages\n6-12.\nDrop-in.\nUpcoming Programs:\nMarch 17 - No ASC Ses
 sion - March Break program in place\nMarch 24 - Soccer with Sphero\nMarch 
 31 - Easter Bunny Masks\nSnacks are offered during the After School Club f
 or participants.\nFood may contain or have come into contact with common a
 llergens. Ingredient lists will be available. Snacks are generously suppor
 ted\, in part\, by donors.\nIf you or your child lives with a disability\,
  and requires an accessibility accommodation to participate in this progra
 m\, please contact Accessibility Services by email\, accessibleservices@tp
 l.ca\, or voicemail\, 416-393-7099\, to make a request. Please contact us 
 at least three weeks in advance.
LOCATION:Jones
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696abaf8b0595799c096d1fd
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
