BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ozobots
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T210000Z
UID:69af1e1f1e64afd01e60ee4f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Step into a world of creativity and discovery! In this excitin
 g program\, children learn the basics of coding by playing with Ozobot\, a
  tiny robot that follows the paths they design. Kids draw lines\, add colo
 rful codes\, and watch their robot zoom\, turn\, and perform fun moves. As
  they grow more confident\, they begin exploring simple computer coding to
  teach Ozobot even more amazing tricks.\nRegistration is required. For ag
 es 6-12 only (children outside of this age range will not be able to parti
 cipate).\n*For all registered Children's programs at Malvern\, there is a 
 grace period of 10 minutes. After the first 10 minutes of a program\, spot
 s will be given to waiting customers.*\nInformation Collection Notice:\nTh
 e personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Lib
 rary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). 
 The information will only be used for event and program registration\, del
 ivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your informa
 tion can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397
 -5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Malvern\, Community room.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69af1e1f1e64afd01e60ee4f
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
