DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260504T203000Z
UID:69975d87a5d80ac49271e8ac@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Artist Sharon Kawabata demonstrates and teaches how to turn sc
 rap paper\, old magazines/ads into classic origami pieces: crane\, butterf
 ly\, fish\, etc\, using local animals for inspiration and the creation of 
 animal origami as the primary projects.\nPaper folding can be a relaxing p
 rocess\, like many crafts once the skill has been acquired repetition may 
 be a calming result. ​\nFor school-aged children and their caregivers. A
 ll materials provided. Drop-in.\nUnfortunately\, we cannot accommodate any
  large groups/daycares for this program.\nIf you identify as a person with
  a disability and require an accessibility accommodation to participate in
  this program\, please contact Accessibility Services by email\, accessibl
 eservices@tpl.ca\, or voicemail\, 416-393-7099\, to make a request. Please
  contact us at least three weeks in advance.
LOCATION:Jones\, Children's area
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69975d87a5d80ac49271e8ac
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
