BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Astronomy and the Cosmos:  The Growth Spurt of the Early Universe
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T223000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T000000Z
UID:69a60b6b81b67dfe32a9f6bf@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a discussion with Simran Nerval on the birth of th
 e known universe.  In this discussion\, you will learn why scientists thin
 k that the universe is expanding\, how they measure and understand cosmic 
 radiation\, and how this shapes our understanding of the structure of the 
 universe.\nSimran Nerval is a final year PhD candidate at the Dunlap Insti
 tute and Department of Astronomy and Astrophysics at the University of Tor
 onto.  Her studies focus on a time period known as inflation\, the exponen
 tial expansion of the universe within a fraction of a second after the Big
  Bang.  Alongside her research\, she runs coding and astronomy camps for m
 arginalized high school students.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 2/3\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a60b6b81b67dfe32a9f6bf
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
