BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Coding with Python III
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T220000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T000000Z
UID:6974f07e834cbb3dea290d18@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Python is an open source programming language that is used for
  creating web applications\, web content\, mathematics and system scriptin
 g. In this follow up course we will really start to stretch our legs in Py
 thon\, designing and implementing some simple Object Oriented Programming 
 data structures. Key takeaways will include a working knowledge of Python 
 classes and objects.\nThis class is for beginners but assumes you have a b
 asic understanding of Python or have attended Coding with Python I and II.
 \nRegistration will start 2 weeks before this class. Computers will be pro
 vided.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this f
 orm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries 
 Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be use
 d for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions 
 about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerli
 ne staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toron
 to ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Riverdale\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6974f07e834cbb3dea290d18
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
