SUMMARY:Unconventional Materials: An Osborne Collection Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T040000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260601T035959Z
UID:698cfed31e64afd01e5acb6d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:An exhibition of intricately crafted books\, artworks and much
  more. The Unconventional Materials exhibit highlights the use of unconven
 tional techniques and materials in children’s literature\, featuring his
 torical and modern examples.\nVisit the Osborne Collection to experience o
 ur exhibit featuring items such as plasticine art by Barbara Reid\, dioram
 as and panoramas\, postcards and other ephemera\, and hornbooks and battle
 dores.\nLocated on the 4th floor of the Lillian H. Smith Branch. Free. All
  are welcome. Registration is not required.\nThe exhibit can be viewed dur
 ing the Osborne Collection's open hours. Contact the Osborne Collection at
  416-393-7753 or email osstaff@tpl.ca for more information.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Osborne Collection of Early Children's Books. 
 4th floor. The exhibit is open during the same hours as the branch.
