BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to Pixilart.com
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T200000Z
UID:69b312b581b67dfe32ac2439@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Pixilart.com is a website dedicated to allowing artists a plat
 form to create\, share artwork\, challenge each other to draw about certai
 n topics\, join theme-centred groups\, discuss pixel art\, etc. It present
 s itself as a free and easy-to-use alternative to programs like Aseprite a
 nd Photoshop\, with both a built-in online editor and an active community 
 to post your work to.\nIt can be used to create video game sprites\, pixel
  art\, cartoon icons for a social media profile\, or a GIF animation to il
 lustrate a blog entry. This workshop focuses on creating simple images of
  long hair\, flags\, leaves\, etc and exploring how they might blow in the
  wind.\nRegistration\nis required and\nbegins April 14th at 12:30pm.\nNote
 : Your spot will\nnot be guaranteed after 5 minutes of the start of the pr
 ogram.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this f
 orm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries 
 Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be use
 d for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions 
 about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerli
 ne staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toron
 to ON M4W 2G8
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, 2nd Floor - eLearning Lab
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b312b581b67dfe32ac2439
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
