BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Innovator in Residence Kick-Off Party!
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T160000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T180000Z
UID:69a5f4f98089f23c675f5344@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:What happens when a professional composer with over 25 years i
 n film and television music meets artificial intelligence? It's complicate
 d.\nJoin Joel S. Silver\, TPL's Spring 2026 Innovator in Residence\, for t
 he launch of a 12-week residency exploring AI and music production at Fair
 view's Digital Innovation Hub. Joel has composed music for productions acr
 oss CBC\, Netflix\, and NBC\, and has spent the last decade navigating AI'
 s growing role in the creative process — sometimes embracing it\, someti
 mes wrestling with it\, and always asking hard questions about what it mea
 ns for musicians and creators.\nIn this opening event\, Joel will share hi
 s journey from traditional composing to working with AI tools\, including 
 live examples of how he's used AI in his own professional music. Then it's
  your turn - you'll get a chance to try AI music tools for yourself and he
 ar what they can do. Whether you're a musician\, a curious beginner\, or s
 omeone with strong opinions about AI\, this is your invitation to join the
  conversation.\nThis program is part of the Innovator in Residence (AI and
  Music Production) program\, which is designed to help beginner and interm
 ediate learners build knowledge and creative skills and get hands-on with 
 current AI tools in music production and learn about the history\, copyrig
 ht and ethics of generative music. For more information and a full list of
  programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/airesident\n.
LOCATION:Fairview\, 1st Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a5f4f98089f23c675f5344
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
