DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T200000Z
UID:699769994a9fd98b7f7f1fcb@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Explore how to handle and shoot DSLR and Mirrorless cameras wh
 ile learning the basics of how to take a great photo.\nIf you've ever want
 ed to up your photography game\, whether you just want to get better at ta
 king pictures with your phone\, or you want to graduate to a professional 
 DSLR or mirrorless camera\, join us for a class on the basics of photograp
 hy. We will go over the basic settings that go into a good photo as well a
 s talking about camera settings\, lenses\, and lighting\nCamera equipment 
 will be provided for this class. Participants are also welcome to bring th
 eir own camera.\nRegistration is required.\nInformation Collection Notice:
 \nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public
  Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(
 d). The information will only be used for event and program registration\,
  delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your inf
 ormation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416
 -397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Bagshaw Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699769994a9fd98b7f7f1fcb
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
