BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Princess Storytime
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T150000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T153000Z
UID:696aadf1707481383706e3c0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a magical Princess Storytime led by Miss Internati
 onal Canada: Rachel Murgel! Dressed in her crown and sash\, our special gu
 est will read enchanting tales and share inspiring messages about kindness
 \, confidence\, and following your dreams. Perfect for little princes and 
 princesses.\nCostumes encouraged!\nRachel Murgel is Miss International Can
 ada 2025. She represented Canada and placed top 10 in the Miss Internation
 al competition which took place in Japan in November. Having graduated fro
 m McMaster University with a Bachelor of Arts and Science\, and a double m
 inor in Business and English Literature\, she is passionate about ensuring
  equal opportunity for children around the world through education and lit
 eracy.\nDrop in. No registration required.
LOCATION:Hillcrest\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696aadf1707481383706e3c0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Storytime with Maggie Knaus: Eleanor's Moon
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T150000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T153000Z
UID:696aad2a30cbd582eff53c40@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the love of family during this March Break by joinin
 g us and author Maggie Knaus for her reading of "Eleanor's Moon"\; an inte
 rgenerational story that explores the bond between a young girl and her gr
 andfather and the love they share for the moon.\nMaggie Knaus is a photogr
 apher and artist and serves as an executive of the Friends of the Osborne 
 Collection of Early Children’s Books. Eleanor’s Moon is her first pict
 ure book. Originally from Washington DC\, she now lives in Toronto.\nDrop 
 in. No registration required.
LOCATION:Hillcrest\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696aad2a30cbd582eff53c40
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Caribbean Storytime with Yolanda T. Marshall
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T190000Z
UID:696aac5d1a992737378fde62@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join Yolanda T. Marshall for a Caribbean storytime. We will re
 ad\nMarching North\nand will be introduced to the remarkable legacy of Car
 ibbean soldiers who served and fought for Canada. Followed by a reading of
  "\nBrown Girl in the Snow\n" as we sing and dance to a popular Caribbean 
 folk song.\nYolanda T. Marshall is an award-winning Guyanese-born Canadian
  author and columnist. She is also the author of over 20 books\, including
  Brown Girl in the Snow\, A Piece of Black Cake for Santa\, Sweet Sorrel S
 tand\, What's in the Cookie Tin?\, C is for Carnival\, Hot Cross Buns for 
 Everyone and My Soca Birthday Party: with Jollof Rice and Steel Pans. This
  traditionally published author writes diverse\, inclusive\, and festive c
 hildren’s literature that represents the African/Caribbean diaspora.\nDr
 op in. No registration required.
LOCATION:Hillcrest\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696aac5d1a992737378fde62
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
