DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T210000Z
UID:695818bdc719ac98c335c427@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us in the Youth Hub this March Break for a Rubik's Cube P
 ixel Art workshop led by Mikael Taieb. Combine creativity and problem-solv
 ing by using Rubik's Cubes to create vibrant pixel art portraits. Particip
 ants will learn basic cube-solving techniques while developing spatial awa
 reness\, logic\, and artistic skills in a fun\, hands-on environment. The 
 program fosters teamwork\, patience\, and confidence through engaging\, ac
 cessible activities.\nThis program is part of Youth Hub service. Youth Hub
 s are a welcoming place for teens after school and in the summer\, where h
 elpful staff are always available. Free\, nutritious snacks are offered d
 aily. Drop by a branch with a\nYouth Hub\nor call the branch to find out 
 more.
LOCATION:Maria A. Shchuka\, Youth Hub
