BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Journalling Workshop for Teens
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T220000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T000000Z
UID:6984ace28b29ea2800ce0d84@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Through writing\, painting and collage art journaling is a way
  of expressing yourself and stepping away from life for a couple of hours.
  For some people\, art journaling is a way to turn off their brains\, for 
 others\, it's a way to dig deep into things that are weighing on their min
 ds\, and for some\, it's a way to tap into their creative side.\nThis work
 shop will help get participants started to explore their emotions and expe
 riences freely and at their own pace through fun art activities as they cr
 eate their own journal pages.\nRegistration required. Ages 13+.
LOCATION:Wychwood\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6984ace28b29ea2800ce0d84
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
