BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Metal Embossing: Patterns for the Page
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T190000Z
UID:698243db707481383708ba82@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Through this hands-on workshop\, discover the art of metal emb
 ossing inspired by the patterns and craftsmanship found in the Aga Khan M
 useum’s Collections. Working with copper\, participants will learn simpl
 e yet effective techniques to shape and decorate metal surfaces. Guided by
  the Museum Educators\, participants will design and create their own embo
 ssed bookmark\, exploring how artists across the Islamic world have transf
 ormed metal into objects of both beauty and function for centuries.\nIn co
 llaboration with the Aga Khan Museum.\nThis program is only intended for c
 hildren aged 12 to 13 years old.\nOnline registration is required as space
  is limited.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on 
 this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libr
 aries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only 
 be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Ques
 tions about how the library handles your information can be directed to An
 swerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\,
  Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Parliament Street\, Community Room\,\n2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698243db707481383708ba82
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
