BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Finding New Spaces by Grace Mai Kwai
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260302T050000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T035959Z
UID:69a6ea7ab48451fc3c06559d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout March works by Grace Mai Kwai are on display at Blo
 or Gladstone Library.\nGrace Mai Kwai is an emerging artist and writer bas
 ed in Toronto\, working primarily in oil painting and fiction writing. As 
 a painter\, she is most excited when creating fantasy landscapes and chara
 cters\, often inspired by the colourful and imaginative world she spent he
 r childhood years dreaming up. Her passion for narrative work has led her 
 to also pursue fiction writing\, where she continues to let her imaginatio
 n run freely. Her work is rooted in the female perspective\, centering wom
 en’s voices and lived experiences in ways that challenge objectification
  while embracing emotional complexity. Her narrative work similarly foregr
 ounds the lives of women\, particularly those on the margins\, using ficti
 on as a tool to unravel societal structures and shed a light on underrepre
 sented voices.\nThis exhibit is part of TPL's\nArt Exhibit Space\nprogram.
  Toronto Public Library provides space for local artists to exhibit their 
 work at locations across the city. These exhibits aim to reflect the diver
 se cultural interests of the city and its neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can
  be viewed during\nBloor Gladstone\nLibrary's open hours.\nFree. All are w
 elcome.\nImage credit: Grace Mai Kwai\, Evangeline\nOil on canvas
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a6ea7ab48451fc3c06559d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
