DESCRIPTION:Fight fearsome goblins\, discover ancient treasures and explor
 e a fantasy world with your friends in the Youth Hub! Join us for a fun an
 d collaborative storytelling experience led by a youth hub librarian as th
 e game master.\nNo prior experience is required and new players are welcom
 e to play. Dice and pre-generated character sheets will be provided for al
 l participants.\nFor teens only.\nThis program is part of Youth Hub servic
 e. Youth Hubs are a welcoming place for teens after school and in the summ
 er\, where helpful staff are always available. Free\, nutritious snacks a
 re offered daily. Drop by a branch with a\nYouth Hub\nor call the branch 
 to find out more.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal informatio
 n on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public
  Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will 
 only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation.
  Questions about how the library handles your information can be directed 
 to Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street
 \, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Youth Hub (on the second floor)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699de99f8d5e2d0933614ddd
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
