BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Coding with Python V
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T220000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T000000Z
UID:6974f1ca3cc3e0c9ecb474d2@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Python is an open source programming language that is used for
  creating web applications\, web content\, mathematics and system scriptin
 g. In this follow up course we will take a break from the logical side of 
 back-end development and get our feet wet with a little bit of front-end c
 oding\; we'll make a user interface! Using tkinter\, a popular module for 
 creating user-facing layouts\, we will design and implement a simple but e
 ffective UI for our Python code. This will allow us to run our programs us
 ing another platform other than Terminal.\nThis class is for beginners but
  assumes you have a basic understanding of Python or have attended Coding 
 with Python I\, II\, III\, and IV.\nRegistration will start 2 weeks before
  this class. Computers will be provided.\nInformation Collection Notice:\n
 The personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public L
 ibrary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d)
 . The information will only be used for event and program registration\, d
