BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Youth Hub: Branding
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T210000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T220000Z
UID:698f747481b67dfe32a63df9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Ready to build a brand that’s 100% YOU?\nIn this workshop\, 
 you’ll discover what makes you unique and how to show it with confidence
 . Learn how to create your own brand from scratch—write a strong mission
  statement\, choose your core values\, and set brand guidelines so your vi
 be stays consistent.\nCheck out real businesses started by young entrepren
 eurs just like you—and see how their ideas turned into success stories. 
 Your idea could be next.\nThis workshop is part of the Youth for Entrepren
 eurship program led by the YMCA of Greater Toronto. Through hands-on sessi
 ons\, you’ll gain the digital tools\, financial knowledge\, and creative
  strategies needed to build a business idea from the ground up.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Auditorium (lower level)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698f747481b67dfe32a63df9
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
