DESCRIPTION:LivingWorks safeTALK is a half-day workshop that prepares part
 icipants to recognize when someone might be having thoughts of suicide and
  how to connect them to life-saving support. Learn practical skills to he
 lp someone keep safe and guide them toward further help.\nWho should atten
 d?\nIndividuals aged 15 and up\nPeople who want to support suicide safety 
 in their community\nNo previous training or experience is required. All p
 articipants will receive a\nLivingWorks safeTALK certificate\nupon worksho
 p completion.\nThis program is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Cent
 re’s safeTALK initiative\n.\nGerstein Crisis Centre is solely responsibl
 e for the protection of \npersonal information collected through the progr
 am registration \nprocess.
