BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:3D Design: TinkerCAD 1
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T180000Z
UID:69a6ee05491b809c6f1dc0f6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:All Ages!\nTinkerCAD Part 1. Learn to create your first 3D pro
 ject\, design a personalized item\, and choose colours to print it. Tinker
 CAD is an easy to learn and free browser based 3D design program from Auto
 desk.\nIn this class\, you will:\nLearn how to navigate the TinkerCAD work
 space\, menus\, and views (zoom\, pan\, rotate).\nBuild a clean\, printabl
 e design using accurate sizing\, rulers and measurements\, and simple desi
 gn best practices.\nCustomize your project with text\, cutouts using the h
 ole tool\, and colour choices.\nExport your finished model (STL or OBJ) so
  it can be 3D printed or shared.\nThis class is recommended to be taken fi
 rst before TinkerCAD Part 2
LOCATION:York Woods\, Digital Innovation Hub\, Main Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a6ee05491b809c6f1dc0f6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
