SUMMARY:March Break Teens: Watercolour Trees and Chickens
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T200000Z
UID:696a97186724c63d00ec9344@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:​In this workshop\, artist Anna Redish will show participant
 s a few basic watercolour techniques while having fun making their painti
 ngs. We will be colour mixing to make fun little chickens and learning the
  salt technique to paint a beautiful tree in winter scene. Some of the tec
 hniques we will be exploring are: colour mixing\, wet on wet salt techniqu
 e. This will be a fun two-in-one workshop that is perfect for any level.\n
 Information Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is c
 ollected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, se
 ctions 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for ev
