BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mismatched Socks for World Down Syndrome Day
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T150000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T153000Z
UID:699891b7403a4e5652dcdbc7@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us after Family Storytime on Saturday March 21 to celebra
 te World Down Syndrome Day.\nDid you know that March 21 is World Down Synd
 rome Day? On March 21 people wear mismatched socks to represent diversity\
 , uniqueness\, and because the socks look like chromosomes under a microsc
 ope!\nVisit the library to decorate a pair of mismatched socks. Socks and
  fabric markers will be provided. We will have socks in various children's
  sizes.\nFor children of all ages and their parents/caregivers.\nNo regist
 ration necessary\, however supplies are limited.
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699891b7403a4e5652dcdbc7
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
