UID:699b3fd74dacf581ff7d12e7@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Sea of Life is a 2017 documentary film about filmmaker Julia B
 arnes' journey around the world to save the ecosystems we depend on\, as 
 we come closer to causing a mass extinction in the oceans.\nScheduled for 
 the day after National Canadian Film Day\, in this documentary\, Barnes t
 akes a deep dive into how actions by governments\, businesses and ordinary
  people can all have a drastic impact on sustainability\nThanks to\nReel C
 anada\nfor providing the screening of this film.\nRun time: 88 minutes
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 1
